What kind of Business Profile will be approved quickly?

To ensure a quick approval of your Business Profile, make sure to provide accurate and complete information during the verification process. This includes your company's full address, legal entity name, EHID or DUNS number, primary contact person's name, and phone number. Once you submit these details to adsupport@newsbreak.com with the subject line: Business Verification, our team will conduct a thorough review and update you on your account status. Let me know if you need any more help!

The criteria communicated for business verification include providing your company's full address, legal entity name, EHID or DUNS number, primary contact person's name, and phone number. This information is necessary for our Ad Operations and Trust & Safety teams to verify your account and domain. If you have any more questions or need assistance, feel free to ask!
What is a valid domain name?

A valid domain name is one that is properly registered and owned by your business. It should be unique, not infringe on any trademarks, and accurately represent your brand or business. Make sure it doesn't imitate or replicate existing trademarks to avoid confusion. If you need more details on domain requirements, feel free to ask!

For domain requirements, ensure that your domain name is unique and does not infringe on any existing trademarks. It should accurately represent your business and not imitate or replicate trademarked logos, product names, trade names, or business names of others. This helps avoid consumer confusion and ensures compliance with our policies. If you have further questions or need clarification, feel free to reach out!
